    "topic": "calculus",
    "problem": "What is \\(\\displaystyle\\lim_{x\\to 0}\\frac{\\sin(3x)}{x}\\)?",
    "choices": {"A": "\\(0\\)", "B": "\\(1\\)", "C": "\\(3\\)", "D": "\\(\\infty\\)", "E": "the limit does not exist"},
    "answer": "C",
    "solution": "Write \\(\\frac{\\sin(3x)}{x}=3\\cdot\\frac{\\sin(3x)}{3x}\\). As \\(x\\to 0\\), \\(\\frac{\\sin(3x)}{3x}\\to 1\\), so the limit is \\(\\boxed{3}\\)."
  },
  {
    "source": "gre_style", "contest": "GRE Math Subject", "number": 2, "url": "",
    "topic": "calculus",
    "problem": "Evaluate \\(\\displaystyle\\int_0^{\\pi}\\sin x\\,dx\\).",
    "choices": {"A": "\\(0\\)", "B": "\\(1\\)", "C": "\\(2\\)", "D": "\\(\\pi\\)", "E": "\\(-2\\)"},
    "answer": "C",
    "solution": "\\(\\int_0^{\\pi}\\sin x\\,dx=[-\\cos x]_0^{\\pi}=-\\cos\\pi+\\cos 0=1+1=\\boxed{2}\\)."
  },
  {
    "source": "gre_style", "contest": "GRE Math Subject", "number": 3, "url": "",
    "topic": "sequences_series",
    "problem": "What is the value of \\(\\displaystyle\\sum_{n=1}^{\\infty}\\frac{1}{2^{n}}\\)?",
    "choices": {"A": "\\(\\tfrac12\\)", "B": "\\(1\\)", "C": "\\(2\\)", "D": "\\(\\tfrac32\\)", "E": "it diverges"},
    "answer": "B",
    "solution": "Geometric series with first term \\(a=\\tfrac12\\) and ratio \\(r=\\tfrac12\\): sum \\(=\\frac{a}{1-r}=\\frac{1/2}{1/2}=\\boxed{1}\\)."
  },
  {
    "source": "gre_style", "contest": "GRE Math Subject", "number": 4, "url": "",
    "topic": "sequences_series",
    "problem": "What is the radius of convergence of the power series \\(\\displaystyle\\sum_{n=0}^{\\infty}\\frac{x^{n}}{n!}\\)?",
    "choices": {"A": "\\(0\\)", "B": "\\(1\\)", "C": "\\(e\\)", "D": "\\(\\infty\\)", "E": "\\(\\tfrac1e\\)"},
    "answer": "D",
    "solution": "By the ratio test, \\(\\left|\\frac{a_{n+1}}{a_n}\\right|=\\frac{|x|}{n+1}\\to 0<1\\) for all \\(x\\). The series converges everywhere, so the radius of convergence is \\(\\boxed{\\infty}\\) (indeed the series is \\(e^{x}\\))."
  },
  {
    "source": "gre_style", "contest": "GRE Math Subject", "number": 5, "url": "",
    "topic": "differential_equations",
    "problem": "Solve \\(y'=2y\\) with \\(y(0)=1\\).",
    "choices": {"A": "\\(y=e^{x}\\)", "B": "\\(y=e^{2x}\\)", "C": "\\(y=2e^{x}\\)", "D": "\\(y=e^{x^{2}}\\)", "E": "\\(y=1+2x\\)"},
    "answer": "B",
    "solution": "Separating, \\(\\frac{dy}{y}=2\\,dx\\Rightarrow \\ln|y|=2x+C\\Rightarrow y=Ae^{2x}\\). With \\(y(0)=1\\), \\(A=1\\), so \\(y=\\boxed{e^{2x}}\\)."
  },
  {
    "source": "gre_style", "contest": "GRE Math Subject", "number": 6, "url": "",
    "topic": "differential_equations",
    "problem": "What is the general solution of \\(y''+y=0\\)?",
    "choices": {"A": "\\(c_1e^{x}+c_2e^{-x}\\)", "B": "\\(c_1\\cos x+c_2\\sin x\\)", "C": "\\(c_1+c_2x\\)", "D": "\\(c_1e^{2x}+c_2e^{-2x}\\)", "E": "\\(c_1\\cos 2x+c_2\\sin 2x\\)"},
    "answer": "B",
    "solution": "The characteristic equation is \\(r^{2}+1=0\\), so \\(r=\\pm i\\). The real general solution is \\(\\boxed{c_1\\cos x+c_2\\sin x}\\)."
  },
  {
