    "topic": "linear_algebra",
    "problem": "What is \\(\\det\\begin{pmatrix}1&2\\\\3&4\\end{pmatrix}\\)?",
    "choices": {"A": "\\(-2\\)", "B": "\\(2\\)", "C": "\\(-1\\)", "D": "\\(10\\)", "E": "\\(-10\\)"},
    "answer": "A",
    "solution": "\\(\\det=1\\cdot 4-2\\cdot 3=4-6=\\boxed{-2}\\)."
  },
  {
    "source": "gre_style", "contest": "GRE Math Subject", "number": 8, "url": "",
    "topic": "linear_algebra",
    "problem": "If \\(A\\) is a \\(4\\times 6\\) matrix of rank \\(4\\), what is the dimension of the solution space of \\(Ax=0\\)?",
    "choices": {"A": "\\(0\\)", "B": "\\(1\\)", "C": "\\(2\\)", "D": "\\(4\\)", "E": "\\(6\\)"},
    "answer": "C",
    "solution": "By the rank-nullity theorem, \\(\\text{nullity}=n-\\text{rank}=6-4=\\boxed{2}\\)."
  },
  {
    "source": "gre_style", "contest": "GRE Math Subject", "number": 9, "url": "",
    "topic": "abstract_algebra",
    "problem": "How many elements of order \\(2\\) does the group \\(\\mathbb{Z}/6\\mathbb{Z}\\) (under addition) have?",
    "choices": {"A": "\\(0\\)", "B": "\\(1\\)", "C": "\\(2\\)", "D": "\\(3\\)", "E": "\\(5\\)"},
    "answer": "B",
    "solution": "An element \\(x\\) has order \\(2\\) iff \\(2x\\equiv 0\\pmod 6\\) and \\(x\\neq 0\\). This gives \\(x=3\\) only, so there is \\(\\boxed{1}\\) such element."
  },
  {
    "source": "gre_style", "contest": "GRE Math Subject", "number": 10, "url": "",
    "topic": "abstract_algebra",
    "problem": "How many generators does the cyclic group \\(\\mathbb{Z}/8\\mathbb{Z}\\) have?",
    "choices": {"A": "\\(1\\)", "B": "\\(2\\)", "C": "\\(4\\)", "D": "\\(7\\)", "E": "\\(8\\)"},
    "answer": "C",
    "solution": "The generators are the residues coprime to \\(8\\): \\(\\{1,3,5,7\\}\\). Their count is \\(\\varphi(8)=\\boxed{4}\\)."
  },
  {
    "source": "gre_style", "contest": "GRE Math Subject", "number": 11, "url": "",
    "topic": "real_analysis",
    "problem": "What is \\(\\sup\\left\\{\\,1-\\tfrac1n : n\\in\\mathbb{N}\\,\\right\\}\\)?",
    "choices": {"A": "\\(0\\)", "B": "\\(\\tfrac12\\)", "C": "\\(1\\)", "D": "\\(2\\)", "E": "it does not exist"},
    "answer": "C",
    "solution": "The terms \\(1-\\tfrac1n\\) increase toward \\(1\\) but never reach it. \\(1\\) is an upper bound and no smaller number is, so the supremum is \\(\\boxed{1}\\) (it is not attained)."
  },
  {
    "source": "gre_style", "contest": "GRE Math Subject", "number": 12, "url": "",
    "topic": "real_analysis",
    "problem": "Which of the following functions is uniformly continuous on the open interval \\((0,1)\\)?",
    "choices": {"A": "\\(\\tfrac1x\\)", "B": "\\(\\sin\\!\\left(\\tfrac1x\\right)\\)", "C": "\\(x^{2}\\)", "D": "\\(\\tfrac{1}{1-x}\\)", "E": "\\(\\tfrac{1}{x^{2}}\\)"},
    "answer": "C",
    "solution": "\\(x^{2}\\) extends to a continuous function on the compact interval \\([0,1]\\), hence is uniformly continuous on \\((0,1)\\). The others blow up or oscillate near an endpoint (e.g. \\(1/x\\) and \\(\\sin(1/x)\\) near \\(0\\), \\(1/(1-x)\\) near \\(1\\)), so they are not uniformly continuous. Answer: \\(\\boxed{x^{2}}\\)."
  },
  {
    "source": "gre_style", "contest": "GRE Math Subject", "number": 13, "url": "",
    "topic": "probability",
    "problem": "A fair coin is flipped \\(3\\) times. What is the probability of getting exactly \\(2\\) heads?",
    "choices": {"A": "\\(\\tfrac18\\)", "B": "\\(\\tfrac14\\)", "C": "\\(\\tfrac38\\)", "D": "\\(\\tfrac12\\)", "E": "\\(\\tfrac34\\)"},
    "answer": "C",
    "solution": "There are \\(\\binom{3}{2}=3\\) favorable outcomes out of \\(2^{3}=8\\), so the probability is \\(\\boxed{\\tfrac38}\\)."
  },
  {
    "source": "gre_style", "contest": "GRE Math Subject", "number": 14, "url": "",
    "topic": "probability",
    "problem": "What is the expected value of a single roll of a fair six-sided die?",
    "choices": {"A": "\\(3\\)", "B": "\\(3.5\\)", "C": "\\(4\\)", "D": "\\(6\\)", "E": "\\(21\\)"},
    "answer": "B",
    "solution": "\\(E[X]=\\frac{1+2+3+4+5+6}{6}=\\frac{21}{6}=\\boxed{3.5}\\)."
  },
