    "problem": "What is the value of \\(e^{i\\pi}\\)?",
    "choices": {"A": "\\(1\\)", "B": "\\(-1\\)", "C": "\\(i\\)", "D": "\\(0\\)", "E": "\\(-i\\)"},
    "answer": "B",
    "solution": "By Euler's formula \\(e^{i\\theta}=\\cos\\theta+i\\sin\\theta\\), so \\(e^{i\\pi}=\\cos\\pi+i\\sin\\pi=-1\\). Answer: \\(\\boxed{-1}\\)."
